Complete Recycling Solutions is focusing on the needs for recycling of lighting and electronic wastes.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: Complete Recycling Solutions is established in 2002, focusing on the need for recycling of lighting and electronic wastes. CRS' processing and R2 certified facility is located in Fall River, Massachusetts near the intersection of I-195 and route 24; providing easy access to surrounding areas.  CRS also has a satellite collection facility located in Somerset, NJ; ensuring a high level of service for all of its customers. Their company's ownership has over 50 years of combined industry experience, ensuring the ability to properly service and create the recycling solution required for anyone. CRS has built it's company on service and is committed to surpassing your recycling service expectations.  Their company recycles all mercury-bearing lamps, electronics and cathode ray tubes (CRT's), mercury devices, batteries, PCB and Non-PCB Lighting ballasts. CRS carries 5 million dollars of Pollution Liability Insurance. CRS operates under a Class C, Level III recycling permit, issued by the Massachusetts Department of Environmental Protection. CRS has R2 Certification (EPA's responsible recycling standard) for electronics recycling. CRS owns and operates state of the art lamp recycling and mercury distillation equipment. This equipment automatically disassembles various lamp types into their basic components to be re-used in the marketplace. CRS owns and operates a hard drive shredder, ensuring secure data destruction onsite.  CRS provides its customers with "certificates of reclamation" as proof of recycling, in accordance with applicable Federal regulations 40 CFR. CRS offers Pick-Up Service on a schedule that meets your company's needs. Currently, their company has four 24' box trucks and numerous 48' trailers; all of which are equipped with power lift gates. Primarily servicing the Northeastern US, they can have one of their trucks at your location promptly. They can also deliver UN DOT-Approved packaging for recycling.

Full Description: Nestled among the vineyard dotted hills of Cayuga Lake; Buttonwood Grove Winery offers visitors a unique experience for wine connoisseurs and novices alike. We invite you to join us for a wine tasting and let your journey through wine country become an experience not soon forgotten!  Planted on land long recognized as being ideal for grape cultivation, our vineyard produces classic European grape varieties such as Chardonnay, Riesling, Cabernet Franc, and Cabernet Sauvignon. The spacious tasting room overlooks sweeping views of Cayuga Lake and provides the perfect backdrop for tasting our award winning wines or browsing the gift shop in search of a wine country souvenir.  Buttonwood Grove Winery is now also one of a handful of wineries with lodging facilities for overnight accommodations. Guests can enjoy a peaceful evening in a log cabin and wake to the sun peaking over the hills and shining across the vineyard.  The view, arguably the most breath taking on Cayuga Lake, provides the perfect backdrop for a leisurely picnic out on the deck, or afternoon hike to our own waterfall, or an evening of entertainment. No matter what your plans are in the Finger Lakes, whether you visit for an hour or for the night, Buttonwood Grove Winery offers a little something for everyone.

When it comes to the quality of the work, you can expect it to get done right, the first time.  That being said, no one is 100% perfect, but we do have a 100% guarantee, that we will get it right and do right by you, our client! We know that keeping a car in tip-top shape is a hassle, and even more so when you need to take time out of the day to go get it done.  Instead, let us come to you, and give you some peace of mind that your car will continue giving you years of us when repaired right!

Description: AutoScout represents the state-of-the-art in football video technology. It automatically breaks down game film.
Full Description: In June 2009, AutoScout was conceptualized in Champaign, Illinois. A team let by Narendra and Shaunak conducted initial research and development for 19 months which resulted in a proof of concept prototype. This prototype was taken to and validated by the market as useful and needed. In December 2010, AutoScout research and development efforts shifted to the Advanced Digital Sciences Center (ADSC), a research arm of the University of Illinois in Singapore. The “Semantic Analysis of Sports Video” project was officially approved in August 2011. From August 2011 through Spring of 2014, the senior management team conducted research and development for AutoScout as well as other computer vision applications. Efforts resulted in, among other things, three different solutions for (American) football video analysis backed by one patent (pending), three technical disclosures, and eleven top conference and journal publications. In December 2013, AutoScout Inc. was officially formed. As of Summer 2014, full-time research, development, and commercialization efforts are underway in the University Of Illinois’s noted incubator EnterpriseWorks.
Founders: Bernard Ghanem, Indriyati Atmosukarto, Narendra Ahuja, Shaunak Ahuja, Tiazhu Zhang

Full Description: Forthright REI, LLC is the holding company for the Houston regional franchise of Commission Express. Commission Express is the largest provider of business capital to real estate agents and brokers in the United States. Forthright REI bought the exclusive rights to this business in 2008 and has consistently grown the business year over year from between 10% - 30%.     Commission Express provides commission advance services to real estate professionals and has been doing so since 1992. Forthright REI opened the Houston office of Commission Express in 2008 and today services hundreds of customers.    The company is seeking additional capital in order to expand it's customer base. With over 30,000 agents in Houston and 12,000 plus commissions paid monthly, there is plenty of room to expand. Commission Express is the only company of it's type with a office in Houston and, with 7 years of experience, is well positioned to penetrate further into this market.     The Texas real estate market is vibrant and Forthright is sitting right on top of it with a service that is crucial to this sector. The company has almost a decade of growth and is a safe place for investors to earn an above average rate of return on their funds.
